The paper proposes a neural architecture search algorithm for image classification tasks, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The algorithm involves selecting atomic blocks and dynamically selecting them during training, which suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of FLOPS configurations, which suggests that it may belong to the neural engineering (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes an end-to-end approach for searching and training the target architecture, which suggests that it may also belong to the distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-category.
